Control Statements
------------------
Using Control statements we can control the execution of our code.

Types  - 3
	1. Conditional Statements
	2. Looping/Iterative statements
	3. Jumping Statements

	
1. Conditional Statements - 4 types
it is use to execute set of statements based upon certain conditions.
		1. If 
		2. If Else 
		3. Nested If Else
		4. Switch Case
		
1) If - Syntax
	
	if(condition)
	{
	Statements;
	}

2) If Else - Syntax

	if(condition)
	{				
	Statements;		//for the single statement we can remove brackets
	}
	else
	{
	Statements;
	}
	
If Else Ladder
---------------
	if(condition)
	{				
	Statements;		
	}
	else if(condition)	//We can put N number of conditions
	{
	Statements;
	}
	else
	{
	Statements;
	}

3) Nested If Else - Syntax (One If condition can have another If condition)

	if(condition)
	{				
		if(condition)
		{
		Statements;
		}
		else
		{
		Statements;
		}		
	}
	else
	{
	Statements;
	}
	
4) Switch Case Statement - We use this when me deal with more number of conditions
	
	switch(variable)
	{
	Case value1: statements;
	Case value2: statements;
	Case value3: statements;
	default: statements;
	}

Assignments
-----------
1) Largest of 2 numbers (if..else, ternary operator)
2) Smallest of 3 numbers
3) Print week number based on week name(Switch Case)
	
	
	
	